result.execSummary:
The defendant Kendrum Chambers was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Kendrum Chambers is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Kendrum Chambers was found guilty of Strangulation and Suffocation [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments, Domestic Abuse Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.235(1).
  • Kendrum Chambers was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct - Domestic Abuse Repeater [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Repeater, Domestic Abuse Assessments], an unclassified felony, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

AS TO COUNTS 2 AND 3:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on motion of State, Court ordered charges dismissed.  
.
AS TO COUNTS 1 AND 4 AS AMENDED:  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he/she is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  
*
Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.  Statements by each counsel and defendant as to sentencing.  
AS TO COUNT 1:  Court sentenced defendant to serve a Term of Imprisonment of 6 YEARS in the Wisconsin State Prison, concurrent with any other sentence; credit for 76 days served.  Court ordered 2 YEARS Initial Term Of Confinement and 4 YEARS Extended Supervision.
.
AS TO COUNT 4:  Court sentenced defendant to serve a Term of Imprisonment of 2 YEARS in the Wisconsin State Prison, concurrent with any other sentence; credit for 76 days served.  Court ordered 1 YEAR Initial Term Of Confinement and 1 YEAR Extended Supervision.

Court found defendant not eligible for Challenge Incarceration or Earned Release Programs.

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
- No further violations of the law.
- Complete batterer's intervention program.
- Attend parenting classes.
- Mental health evaluation; take all prescribed medications.
- AODA assessment; comply with any treatment.
- Maintain absolute sobriety; random screens.
- Attend treatment and/or counseling as determined.
- No contact with victim during the entire sentence unless approved by agent.
- 3rd party contact for the purpose of child visitation.
- Obtain/maintain employment.
- No contact with firearms.
- Pay all costs, surcharges and supervision fees.  The Court ordered that all court costs, fines, surcharges and/or restitution be paid through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision. DOC shall collect those sums.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment and/or tax intercept or other means.
- Restitution to be determined at a hearing on 6/23/15 at 1:30 pm.
